00:46:06.260 --> 00:46:08.330
Good catch.

00:46:08.330 --> 00:46:11.810
AUDIENCE: Hey, have you
guys ever considered

00:46:11.810 --> 00:46:14.180
playing another system other
than the various editions

00:46:14.180 --> 00:46:18.170
of D&amp;D. Has there been
any interest in that?

00:46:18.170 --> 00:46:19.500
MATTHEW MERCER: Oh, yeah.

00:46:19.500 --> 00:46:22.099
D&amp;D is what our main
campaign is, largely

00:46:22.099 --> 00:46:23.640
because that's just
where we started,

00:46:23.640 --> 00:46:26.169
and that's where
the world has gone.

00:46:26.169 --> 00:46:27.710
And it makes sense
within that space.

00:46:27.710 --> 00:46:30.620
But we've done a lot of
one-shots and a lot of side

00:46:30.620 --> 00:46:33.151
games where we've delved into--

00:46:33.151 --> 00:46:35.150
One of what my favorite
systems is "Dead Lands."

00:46:35.150 --> 00:46:36.470
TRAVIS WILLINGHAM:
Oh, it's so good.

00:46:36.470 --> 00:46:37.580
MATTHEW MERCER: I
prefer OG "Dead Lands,"

00:46:37.580 --> 00:46:39.788
but I ran a "Savage Worlds,"
the newer version of it,

00:46:39.788 --> 00:46:43.810
